A Daemon should -
- be started from the command line
- accept port arguements
- couple 2 chatters
- allow for a chatter to quit
- allow for a queue of chatters
- use the current servers IP

A Chatter should -
- be able to choose a server/daemon
- be able to join a chat
- be able to leave a chat
- be able to chat
- be put into a queue when starting the chatr client
- be put back into a queue when a chat is finished(disconnected)
